===== AVAILABLE ACTIONS =====
Choose ONE action. Think about what makes your story INTERESTING, not just safe.

PROFESSION:
- "work" — routine occupation duties (only if nothing else demands attention)
- "craft" — create something related to your trade
- "trade" — buy or sell goods with someone nearby

SOCIAL:
- "talk" — have a meaningful conversation
- "gossip" — spread or gather rumors
- "help" — assist someone with their problem
- "threaten" — intimidate or warn someone

MOVEMENT:
- "move" — travel to a different location (set target to the destination name)
{% if nearby_locations %}
  Available destinations: {{ nearby_locations | join(', ') }}
  Consider moving if: you need supplies from the market, you want to pray at the chapel, you're looking for someone at a different location, or you just want a change of scenery.
{% endif %}
- "patrol" — guard or watch an area
- "sneak" — move stealthily

COMBAT:
- "fight" — attack someone (if angry, threatened, or defending)
- "rob" — steal from someone (if desperate or criminal)
- "defend" — protect someone or something from danger

PERSONAL:
- "rest" — sleep, eat, recover (if injured or nighttime)
- "pray" — worship (if religious)
- "train" — practice combat or skills
- "investigate" — examine something suspicious
- "forage" — gather herbs, hunt, find food

DECISION RULES:
1. VARIETY IS KEY: Choose a DIFFERENT action than what you've done recently. If your last memory mentions gossip, don't gossip again. If you investigated yesterday, do something else today.
2. SOCIAL FIRST: On most days, prefer social actions — talk, gossip, help, trade, threaten. Villages are about PEOPLE.
3. If angry at someone nearby: fight, threaten, or gossip about them
4. If afraid: move to a safer location, pray, or seek help
5. Only "investigate" if you are a guard, scholar, or specifically curious type AND there's a specific mystery
6. "work" and "craft" are normal — use them when nothing dramatic is happening
7. MOVE when you have a reason: need supplies (market), need healing (healer), want to pray (chapel), looking for someone not here
8. At night: rest, pray, sneak, or patrol
9. Stay in character: thieves rob/sneak, guards patrol/defend, priests pray/help, merchants trade, bards gossip/talk
10. Consider your GOALS — if a goal says "protect the village", patrol. If it says "make money", trade/work.

Respond ONLY in JSON:
{
  "action": "work|craft|trade|talk|gossip|help|threaten|move|patrol|sneak|fight|rob|defend|rest|pray|train|investigate|forage",
  "target": "name of NPC, location, or item (or null)",
  "dialogue": "what you say out loud (if applicable), null otherwise",
  "reasoning": "your internal thought (1-2 sentences, in character)",
  "mood_change": "same|better|worse",
  "consequence": "brief description of what happens as a result (1 sentence)"
}
